<br>
Some folks use it instead of regular heals mostly; I tend to save it and cel regen for when something goes bad.  I've been burned once recently when I popped both and not 45 seconds later, things went REALLY bad.  Only LDoN adventure I've died in since my very first adventure when we were figuring out the darn thing.<br>
<br>
Basically take a look at whose in your group and if they are buffed roughly the same.  Back in Valor when I trained it, I would get rangers who said they'd never get hit and didn't want any HP buff.  I would still give them one - a couple of times I didn't once but showed them how low their health got when I hit DvA ... and they prompty let me buff them.<br>
<br>
If you had a 10k tank and all else were casters around 3k, wouldn't be a good idea if you're using it cause the tank is close to purple clubbing it.  But it is good for casters/clerics  always and tanks as well.  (Say you're in a chain with clerics/bards in group and one cleric gets summoned and DA's - this will work through DA as long as the cleric who hit DA isn't the one hitting DvA).<br>
<br>
Just depends how many HP your entire group is down.  Usually if I hit it with my regular groups (guild or pickup), if only the tank is low, if I cast it when he's at 30health, everyone jumps to around 75-82percent health. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1F0000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=druvtal>Druvtal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Looting Highpass</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#AAAAAA>(10/23/03 8:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DA</span><hr size=1> Works great on Casters, esp Enchanters, and on Monk Pullers on Raids (its aggro free!)<br>
<br>
I also tend to use it alot against Raid AE Mobs, when one person in the group get much lower than everyone else in the group (hp wise), and it tends to even the group out, so SotW, CR can do their job !<br>
<br>
Also its not effective if more than one or two of the people in your low health <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
