<br>
1) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Used as first heal to avoid aggro</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: I raided a lot, so most of the stuff I was fighting hit relly hard. If your tank doesn't grab aggro INSTANTLY, the mob will often go after the cleric that lands the first heal. So DvA is perfect in that situation, because it has 0 aggro and is capable of healing almost any amount of damage, as long as no one in your group has significantly lower hps than the rest.<br>
<br>
2) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Used as a HOLY SH<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->IT!!! heal</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: DvA has a cast time of 0.5 seconds, faster than any other heal we have. If I'm casting a CH, SL or other long heals, I often duck out of them and hit DvA if I don't think the longer heal will land in time. This also works on other characters... If I'm near the end of a CH on the tank and I see my chanter getting beat on badly, I'll judge how fast they're losing health, let the CH finish on the tank, then DvA instantly after it lands, saving the chanter.<br>
<br>
DvA just takes a bit of practice to use, but it's a fantastic skill once you're accustomed to it. =)<br>
<br>
